&lt;p>University of St Andrews, St Andrews, UK&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Univ. of St Andrews Astronomical Society</title><link>https://astroweaver.github.io/outreach/societies/</link><pubDate>Fri, 09 Jul 2021 10:34:48 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://astroweaver.github.io/outreach/societies/</guid><description>&lt;p>The University of St Andrews Astronomical Society (&lt;a href="https://www.astrosoc.club/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AstroSoc&lt;/a>) was established in 1972 and has grown into one of the largest student-led astronomical societies world-wide, consisting of over 200 paid members annually. We are affiliated with &lt;a href="https://www.astronomerswithoutborders.org/home" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astronomers without Borders&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I re-organized the society as President in 2015 with an updated website, branding, and advertisement schemes. Other roles include:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>2016 &amp;ndash; Observing Director&lt;/li>
&lt;li>2015 &amp;ndash; President&lt;/li>
&lt;li>2014 &amp;ndash; Observing Director&lt;/li>
&lt;li>2013 &amp;ndash; First Year Representative&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;figure >
&lt;div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
&lt;div class="w-100" >&lt;img alt="" srcset="
/outreach/societies/about_hu5222495219925139600.webp 400w,
/outreach/societies/about_hu2146616300488734036.webp 760w,
/outreach/societies/about_hu7918461284304661051.webp 1200w"
src="https://astroweaver.github.io/outreach/societies/about_hu5222495219925139600.webp"
width="760"
height="506"
loading="lazy" data-zoomable />&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;/figure>
&lt;p>We host free stargazing events each Thursday night, from the comfort our of observatory facilities. Open rain or shine, we endevour to showcase the best that the universe has to offer. We have two research-grade telescopes, and many smaller ones. During our weekly stargazing sessions, we use both our 10&amp;quot; Makutov-Cassegrain LX200 and 16&amp;quot; Schmidt-Cassegrain LX200 telescopes to seek out the dimmest stars and distant galaxies.&lt;/p>
&lt;figure >
&lt;div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
&lt;div class="w-100" >&lt;img alt="" srcset="
